\chapter{OneDrive and SharePoint files}

We want to read and write files stored in KTH's OneDrive and SharePoint
sites, and to list the contents of folders. The first constraint is
authentication: we do not want to require a separate Entra application
registration or a client identifier just to move a file.

The project already has a browser-like login stack through [[ladok3]] and
[[weblogin]]. We therefore reuse that authenticated session and talk to
SharePoint's classic REST and list-view endpoints instead of Microsoft Graph.
This keeps the command line workflow close to what already works elsewhere in
the package.


\section{Code overview}

This module becomes [[kthutils.onedrive]]. We add a small session wrapper,
helpers for turning browser URLs into SharePoint REST paths, and three
commands: [[get]], [[ls]], and [[put]].
